Fort_Wayne.Harry A. Keplinger House: Harry A. Keplinger House is a historic home located at Fort Wayne, Indiana. It was built about 1893, and is a 2 1/2-story, Richardsonian Romanesque style brick dwelling with a rock-faced stone foundation. It features a steeply pitched roof and dormers, round two-story towers at each of the front corners with conical roofs, and a one-story front porch connecting the two towers.
